---
import ToolLayout from "@/layouts/ToolLayout.astro";
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Methodology | Landlord Math Toolkit"
  description="How Landlord Math Toolkit approaches assumptions, calculations, and trust-sensitive rent math."
>
  <section class="hero-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
    <h1>Transparent formulas first.</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy">
      These calculators are designed to make the math visible, not hide it. Every tool includes assumptions,
      a worked example, and a short explanation of what the result means.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-copy">
    <article class="detail-card">
      <h2>Principles</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Use straightforward formulas that can be checked by hand.</li>
        <li>Show assumptions directly on the page instead of burying them.</li>
        <li>Separate calculation help from legal, tax, or market advice.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="detail-card">
      <h2>Important note</h2>
      <p>
        These tools provide calculation support only. Lease language, local law, notice rules, fee caps, and
        compliance requirements vary by location and should be verified independently.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</ToolLayout>
